The paper discusses algorithms for tracking multiple targets, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and control systems (cs.SY). The use of probability hypothesis density (PHD) and multi-target multi-Bernoulli (MeMBer) filters suggests a focus on machine learning and probabilistic modeling, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
